				\begin{document}$$ \chi^2 = (\mathbf{x} - \boldsymbol{\theta})^\mathrm{T} \mathbf{V}^{-1} (\mathbf {x} - \boldsymbol{\theta}) $$\end{document} where V−1 is the inverse of the covariance matrix V, and θ is the product of the unit vector and θ.

